  "A projectile is launched at 40 m/s at an angle of 50 degrees above the horizontal. Its position is given by x(t) = 40 cos(50)t and y(t) = 40 sin(50)t - 4.9t^2. Using cos(50) = 0.643 and sin(50) = 0.766, at what time does the projectile reach its maximum height?": "",
